thread.title: Large earthquake rattles Papua New Guinea

title: Large earthquake rattles Papua New Guinea
text:
Large earthquake rattles Papua New Guinea Published 1 Hour Ago Reinhard Dirsheri | Ullstein Bild | Getty Images Mangrove trees in Papua New Guinea's Pacific Ocean. 
A large earthquake has struck the middle of Papua New Guinea. 
The U.S. Geological Survey says the magnitude-7.5 quake hit about 89 kilometers (55 miles) southwest of Porgera early Monday in the Pacific island nation. 
It wasn't immediately clear if there was damage. The Geological Survey website had 19 reports of feeling the quake, including some saying the shaking was violent.
